`Effect.all` runs every effect and fails the whole computation as soon as one step fails. `Effect.partition` runs every effect and always succeeds — it returns a `[failures, successes]` tuple in the `A` channel so the caller can report every failure instead of stopping on the first one. Use `Effect.all` when a single failure invalidates the batch; use `Effect.partition` for independent items where you want to know which worked and which didn't.

```typescript
