Wrapping the clock as a service makes time injectable. In production you get wall-clock time from the default `Clock` layer; in tests you swap in `TestClock`, which lets you advance virtual time deterministically and assert on time-sensitive behaviour without `sleep`-ing in real life. A direct `Date.now()` ties your code to the real clock and makes time-based logic flaky to test.

